      <section eId="sec_9_12_5">
        <num>9-12-5</num>
        <content>
          <p>In a proper case, the superior court may mold the verdict so as to do full justice to the parties in the same manner as a decree in equity.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 3482; Code 1868, § 3504; Code 1873, § 3562; Code 1882, § 3562; Civil Code 1895, § 5333; Civil Code 1910, § 5928; Code 1933, § 110-106.)</p>
